  </sect2>

  <sect2>
 <!--
   <title>Changes</title>
-->
  <title>变化</title>
   <!--
<para>
    Below you will find a detailed account of the changes between
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 9.1 and the previous major
    release.
   </para>
-->
<para>
   下面你将发现在<productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 9.1 
   和以前主要发布之间的变化的详细列表。
</para>

   <sect3>
 <!--
    <title>Server</title>
-->
   <title>服务器</title>
    <sect4>
<!--
     <title>Performance</title>
-->
   <title>性能</title>
   
   
     <itemizedlist>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Support unlogged tables using the <literal>UNLOGGED</>
        option in <link linkend="SQL-CREATETABLE"><command>CREATE
        TABLE</></link> (Robert Haas)
       </para>
-->
<para>
    支持
在<link linkend="SQL-CREATETABLE"><command>CREATE TABLE</></link>中
使用<literal>UNLOGGED</>选项的未记录表(Robert Haas)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        Such tables provide better update performance than regular tables,
        but are not crash-safe: their contents are automatically cleared in
        case of a server crash.  Their contents do not propagate to
        replication slaves, either.
       </para>
-->
<para>
   这个表提供了比常规表更好的更新性能，但是不安全：它们内容在
   服务器崩溃的情况下被自动清除。
   也不会被传送到备份子服务器。
   
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Allow <literal>FULL OUTER JOIN</literal> to be implemented as a
        hash join, and allow either side of a <literal>LEFT OUTER JOIN</>
        or <literal>RIGHT OUTER JOIN</> to be hashed (Tom Lane)
       </para>
-->
<para>
   允许<literal>FULL OUTER JOIN</literal>作为哈希连接被实现，
   并且允许<literal>LEFT OUTER JOIN</>或者
   <literal>RIGHT OUTER JOIN</>的一侧被哈希(Tom Lane)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        Previously <literal>FULL OUTER JOIN</literal> could only be
        implemented as a merge join, and <literal>LEFT OUTER JOIN</literal>
        and <literal>RIGHT OUTER JOIN</literal> could hash only the nullable
        side of the join.  These changes provide additional query optimization
        possibilities.
       </para>
-->
<para>
   以前<literal>FULL OUTER JOIN</literal>只能作为合并连接被实现，
   并且<literal>LEFT OUTER JOIN</literal>和
   <literal>RIGHT OUTER JOIN</literal>可以哈希连接空侧。
   这些变化提供了额外查询优化可能性。
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Merge duplicate fsync requests (Robert Haas, Greg Smith)
       </para>
-->
<para>
   合并复制fsync请求(Robert Haas, Greg Smith)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        This greatly improves performance under heavy write loads.
       </para>
-->
<para>
   这大大提高了大量写入重载下性能。
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Improve performance of <link
        linkend="guc-commit-siblings"><varname>commit_siblings</></link>
        (Greg Smith)
       </para>
-->
<para>
    提高
<link linkend="guc-commit-siblings"><varname>commit_siblings</></link>
的性能(Greg Smith)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        This allows the use of <varname>commit_siblings</varname> with
        less overhead.
       </para>
-->
<para>
    这允许较少开销的<varname>commit_siblings</varname>的使用。
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Reduce the memory requirement for large ispell dictionaries
        (Pavel Stehule, Tom Lane)
       </para>
-->
<para>
    减少大的ispell词典存储需求(Pavel Stehule, Tom Lane)
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Avoid leaving data files open after <quote>blind writes</>
        (Alvaro Herrera)
       </para>
-->
<para>
    避免<quote>盲写</>后将数据文件打开(Alvaro Herrera)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        This fixes scenarios in which backends might hold files open long
        after they were deleted, preventing the kernel from reclaiming
        disk space.
       </para>
-->
<para>
    这修复它们被删除后后端保持文件打开时间，防止内核回收磁盘空间。
</para>
      </listitem>

     </itemizedlist>

    </sect4>

    <sect4>
<!--
     <title>Optimizer</title>
   -->
     <title>优化器</title>
     <itemizedlist>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Allow inheritance table scans to return meaningfully-sorted
        results (Greg Stark, Hans-Jurgen Schonig, Robert Haas, Tom Lane)
       </para>
-->
<para>
    允许继承表扫描返回有意义的排序结果
(Greg Stark, Hans-Jurgen Schonig, Robert Haas, Tom Lane)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        This allows better optimization of queries that use <literal>ORDER
        BY</>, <literal>LIMIT</>, or <literal>MIN</>/<literal>MAX</> with
        inherited tables.
       </para>
-->
<para>
    这允许使用
<literal>ORDER BY</>，<literal>LIMIT</>
或者带有继承表的<literal>MIN</>/<literal>MAX</>
的查询的更好优化。
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
         Improve GIN index scan cost estimation (Teodor Sigaev)
       </para>
-->
<para>
    提高GIN索引扫描成本估计(Teodor Sigaev)
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Improve cost estimation for aggregates and window functions (Tom Lane)
       </para>
-->
<para>
   提高聚合和window函数成本估计(Tom Lane)
</para>
      </listitem>

     </itemizedlist>

    </sect4>

    <sect4>
<!--
     <title>Authentication</title>
-->
   <title>认证</title>
     <itemizedlist>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Support host names and host suffixes
        (e.g. <literal>.example.com</>) in <link
        linkend="auth-pg-hba-conf"><filename>pg_hba.conf</></link>
        (Peter Eisentraut)
       </para>
-->
<para>
    在<link linkend="auth-pg-hba-conf"><filename>pg_hba.conf</></link>
中支持host名字和host后缀(比如<literal>.example.com</>)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        Previously only host <acronym>IP</> addresses and <acronym>CIDR</>
        values were supported.
       </para>
-->
<para>
   先前只支持host <acronym>IP</> 地址和<acronym>CIDR</>值。
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Support the key word <literal>all</> in the host column of <link
        linkend="auth-pg-hba-conf"><filename>pg_hba.conf</></link>
        (Peter Eisentraut)
       </para>
-->
<para>
   在<link linkend="auth-pg-hba-conf"><filename>pg_hba.conf</></link>的host列
   支持关键字<literal>all</>(Peter Eisentraut)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        Previously people used <literal>0.0.0.0/0</> or <literal>::/0</>
        for this.
       </para>
-->
<para>
   以前为了这个人们使用
   <literal>0.0.0.0/0</>或者<literal>::/0</>。
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Reject <literal>local</> lines in <link
        linkend="auth-pg-hba-conf"><filename>pg_hba.conf</></link>
        on platforms that don't support Unix-socket connections
        (Magnus Hagander)
       </para>
-->
<para>
   在不支持Unix套接字连接的平台上拒绝
   <link linkend="auth-pg-hba-conf"><filename>pg_hba.conf</></link>中的
   <literal>local</>行(Magnus Hagander)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        Formerly, such lines were silently ignored, which could be surprising.
        This makes the behavior more like other unsupported cases.
       </para>
-->
<para>
   先前，默默忽略这样的行，这可能是令人惊讶的。
   这使得该操作更像其他不支持的情况。
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        Allow <link linkend="gssapi-auth"><acronym>GSSAPI</></link>
        to be used to authenticate to servers via <link
        linkend="sspi-auth"><acronym>SSPI</></link> (Christian Ullrich)
       </para>
-->
<para>
   允许<link linkend="gssapi-auth"><acronym>GSSAPI</></link>
   通过<link linkend="sspi-auth"><acronym>SSPI</></link>用于
   验证到服务器(Christian Ullrich)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        Specifically this allows Unix-based <acronym>GSSAPI</> clients
        to do <acronym>SSPI</> authentication with Windows servers.
       </para>
-->
<para>
    特别是允许基于Unix <acronym>GSSAPI</>客户端执行
伴随Windows服务器的<acronym>SSPI</>认证。
</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
       <!--
<para>
        <link linkend="auth-ident"><literal>ident</literal></link>
        authentication over local sockets is now known as
        <link linkend="auth-peer"><literal>peer</literal></link>
        (Magnus Hagander)
       </para>
-->
<para>
   在区域套接字上的<link linkend="auth-ident"><literal>ident</literal></link>
   认证被称为<link linkend="auth-peer"><literal>peer</literal></link>
   (Magnus Hagander)
</para>

       <!--
<para>
        The old term is still accepted for backward compatibility, but since
        the two methods are fundamentally different, it seemed better to adopt
        different names for them.
       </para>
-->
<para>
   该旧的术语仍然接受向后兼容性，但是
   因为这两种方法在根本上是不同的，
   为它们采用不同的名字似乎更好。
</para>
      </listitem>

